                <note rend="inline" type="source">314.115C43/136: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-12T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 12, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. Referring to Department’s telegram of July 10, 3 p.m. The Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs has told me that he will study my memorandum of today<note
                        n="26" xml:id="d147fn26">See <hi rend="italic">Shufeldt Claim</hi>, p.
                        324.</note> regarding Shufeldt and submit the matter to the Cabinet on the
                    16th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
